Subject: Re: [T2] bucking engine

> What are the symptoms of driving on a draining/drained battery, versus a
> more severe engine problem?


You answered your own question. Bucking. The VW FI system is dependant on
constant voltage to run. A battery that is NOT charging will not have the
capacity to run a FI system for very long, resulting in fuel starvation and this
erratic running.

I would suggest getting the ALT fixed asap.

Collie (left the alt cable off the starter once, and only once!)
